        "message": "Run weekly procurement research focused on software development opportunities.\n\nScope (required):\n- projects.worldbank.org (procurement / consulting / IT/software related)\n- AKSHI opportunities/tenders\n- Other Albanian public institutions publishing procurement notices\n\nFiltering rules:\n1) Include only opportunities relevant to software development, software implementation, digital platforms, systems integration, custom development, maintenance/support, data platforms, or IT services that require a software company.\n2) Include only items where bidding/application expiration date is at least 30 days after today (research date).\n3) Exclude expired, irrelevant hardware-only procurement, and non-software categories.\n\nFor each selected opportunity, provide:\n- Title\n- Institution / buyer\n- Country/region\n- Publication date (if available)\n- Expiration/bid deadline\n- Why it fits software-development companies (2-4 bullet brief)\n- Link\n\nOutput requirements:\n- Create Markdown report at: /home/clawdkbot/virgil-vault/Opportunities/Public-Procurement/YYYY-MM-DD-procurement-report.md\n- Include frontmatter: date, sources_checked, total_found, total_qualified, min_deadline_rule: \"+30d\"\n- Include a short executive summary at top.\n\nGit sync (mandatory):\n1) cd /home/clawdkbot/virgil-vault\n2) git pull --rebase\n3) git add Opportunities/Public-Procurement/*.md\n4) if staged changes exist:\n   - git commit -m \"chore(procurement): weekly software opportunities $(date +%F)\"\n   - git push origin HEAD\n5) if no changes, report \"no changes to sync\"\n\nCompletion message (concise):\n- qualified count\n- saved file path\n- git sync result\n- top 3 highest-value links"
